# Standard Form Components

This project has purpose-built components and utilities for phone numbers and addresses. Always use them instead of raw `<Input>` fields.

## Phone Numbers

Use the `PhoneInput` component from `@/components/ui/phone-input` for all phone number fields. It provides a country code selector with flags, E.164 formatting, and international number support.

```tsx
import { PhoneInput } from "@/components/ui/phone-input"
import { isValidPhoneNumber, formatPhoneNumberIntl } from "react-phone-number-input"

// Input
<PhoneInput
  defaultCountry="US"
  value={form.phone}
  onChange={(value) => setForm((f) => ({ ...f, phone: value || "" }))}
/>

// Validation
if (!isValidPhoneNumber(form.phone)) { /* invalid */ }

// Display (on cards, tables, etc.)
formatPhoneNumberIntl(phone) || phone   // "+1 555 123 4567"
```

**Never** use `<Input type="tel">` for phone numbers.

## Addresses (Country, State/Province, Postal Code)

Use the standard location data utilities from `@/lib/location-data`:

```tsx
import { COUNTRIES, getRegionsForCountry, isValidPostalCode } from "@/lib/location-data"
```

### Country — `Select` dropdown

```tsx
<Select value={form.country} onValueChange={(value) =>
  setForm((f) => ({ ...f, country: value, stateProvince: f.country !== value ? "" : f.stateProvince }))
}>
  <SelectTrigger><SelectValue placeholder="Select country" /></SelectTrigger>
  <SelectContent>
    {COUNTRIES.map((c) => (
      <SelectItem key={c.code} value={c.code}>{c.name}</SelectItem>
    ))}
  </SelectContent>
</Select>
```

### State / Province — `StateProvinceCombobox`

Use the `StateProvinceCombobox` component from `@/components/ui/state-province-combobox`. It renders a searchable combobox for US states / CA provinces, falls back to a plain `<Input maxLength={2}>` for other countries, and includes a hidden `<input autocomplete="address-level1">` so browser autofill and password managers (1Password, etc.) can populate the field.

```tsx
import { StateProvinceCombobox } from "@/components/ui/state-province-combobox"

<StateProvinceCombobox
  country={form.country}
  value={form.stateProvince}
  onChange={(val) => setForm((f) => ({ ...f, stateProvince: val }))}
  disabled={false}   // optional
  error={false}      // optional — adds border-destructive styling
/>
```

**Never** build an inline Popover+Command combobox for state/province — always use this component.

### Postal / ZIP Code — contextual label and validation

- Label: `"Postal Code"` for CA, `"ZIP Code"` for US
- Placeholder: `"A1A 1A1"` for CA, `"12345"` for US
- Validate with `isValidPostalCode(value, country)` before submit

### Displaying addresses

Resolve codes to names for display:

```tsx
// State/Province name
getRegionsForCountry(address.country).find((r) => r.code === address.stateProvince)?.name ?? address.stateProvince

// Country name
COUNTRIES.find((c) => c.code === address.country)?.name ?? address.country
```

## Default values

- Phone: `defaultCountry="US"`
- Address country: `"US"` as the default initial value
